'''胃壁細胞'''（{{lang-en|(gastric) parietal cells}}）又稱'''壁細胞、泌酸細胞'''，為分泌[[鹽酸|鹽酸]]及[[內在因子|內在因子]]之上皮細胞。這些細胞都位於[[胃|胃]]之[[胃|胃底]]（{{lang|en|gastric fundus}}）襯裡中之[[胃腺體|胃腺體]]（{{lang|en|gastric glands}}）裡。它們含有從其中HCl通過[[主動運輸|主動運輸]]分泌到胃中的廣泛分泌網絡（稱為[[小管|小管]]）。[[鉀鈉腺苷三磷酸酶|鉀鈉腺苷三磷酸酶]]（{{lang|en|Hydrogen potassium ATPase}}）（H<sup>+</sup>/K<sup>+</sup> ATP酶）是唯一的胃壁細胞及輸送 H<sup>+</sup> 對約300萬至1的濃度梯度，這形成在人體中的最陡的離子梯度。胃壁細胞主要是通過[[組織胺|組織胺]]、[[乙酰胆碱|乙酰胆碱]]與[[胃泌素|胃泌素]]等來自中央區和地方區的兩個調製器的信號來調控（參見“[[#規定性|規定性]]條例”）規定。

== 鹽酸的分泌 ==
===综合性===
鹽酸以下列方式形成：
*氫離子從碳酸的離解而形成的。<!--Water is a very minor source of hydrogen ions in comparison to carbonic acid. Carbonic acid is formed from [[carbon_dioxide|carbon dioxide]] and water by carbonic anhydrase.
* The bicarbonate ion (HCO<sub>3</sub><sup>−</sup>) is exchanged for a chloride ion (Cl<sup>−</sup>) on the basal side of the cell and the bicarbonate diffuses into the venous blood, leading to an [[alkaline_tide|alkaline tide]] phenomenon.-->
*[[鉀|鉀]]（K+）和氯化物（Cl-）的離子擴散到[[胃壁細胞#小管|小管]]。
<!--* Hydrogen ions are pumped out of the cell into the canaliculi in exchange for potassium ions, via the [[hydrogen_potassium_ATPase|H<sup>+</sup>/K<sup>+</sup> ATPase]]. These receptors are increased in number on luminal side by fusion of tubulovesicles during activation of parietal cells and removed during deactivation. This receptor maintains a million fold difference in proton concentration. ATP is provided by the numerous mitochondria. 
-->
要進行氫離子細胞出口的作用，胃腔需保持為高酸性環境。<!--The acidity aids in digestion of food by promoting the unfolding (or [[Denaturation_(biochemistry)|denaturing]]) of ingested [[protein|protein]]s.  As proteins unfold, the [[peptide_bonds|peptide bonds]] linking component [[amino_acids|amino acids]] are exposed.  Gastric HCl simultaneously activates [[pepsinogen|pepsinogen]], an endopeptidase that advances the digestive process by breaking the now-exposed peptide bonds, a process known as [[proteolysis|proteolysis]].
-->

===規定性===
胃壁細胞因應於三類型的[[刺激|刺激]]而來[[分泌|分泌]](secretion)胃酸：<ref>{{cite book|last=Boulpaep|first=Walter|title=Medical Physiology|url=https://archive.org/details/medicalphysiolog0000unse_r1q7|year=2009|publisher=Saunders|location=Philadelphia|isbn=978-1-4160-3115-4|pages=[https://archive.org/details/medicalphysiolog0000unse_r1q7/page/898 898]–899}}</ref>
*[[組織胺|組織胺]]，刺激[[組織胺受體|H<sub>2</sub>組織胺受體]]( histamine receptor)（最顯著的貢獻）。
<!--* [[Acetylcholine|Acetylcholine]], from [[parasympathetic|parasympathetic]] activity via the [[vagus_nerve|vagus nerve]] and enteric nervous system, stimulating [[Muscarinic_acetylcholine_receptor_M3|M<sub>3</sub> receptors]].<ref name="M3 receptor">{{cite web|title=Gastric acid secretion - Homo sapiens|url=http://www.genome.jp/dbget-bin/show_pathway?hsa04971+1131|publisher=KEGG|accessdate=June 1, 2011}}</ref>
* [[Gastrin|Gastrin]], stimulating [[Cholecystokinin_B_receptor|CCK2 receptors]] (least significant contribution, but also causes histamine secretion by local [[Enterochromaffin-like_cell|ECL cells]])
Activation of histamine through H<sub>2</sub> receptor causes increases intracellular cAMP level while Ach through M<sub>3</sub> receptor and gastrin through CCK2 receptor increases intracellular calcium level. These receptors are present on basolateral side of membrane.

Increased cAMP level results in increased protein kinase A. Protein kinase A phosphorylates proteins involved in the transport of [[Hydrogen_potassium_ATPase|H<sup>+</sup>/K<sup>+</sup> ATPase]] from the cytoplasm to the [[cell_membrane|cell membrane]].  This causes resorption of K<sup>+</sup> ions and secretion of H<sup>+</sup> ions. The [[pH|pH]] of the secreted fluid can fall by 0.8.

Gastrin primarily induces acid-secretion indirectly, increasing histamine synthesis in [[Enterochromaffin-like_cell|ECL cells]],<nowiki/>which in turn signal parietal cells via histamine release/H2 stimulation.<ref>Waldum, Helge L., Kleveland, Per M., et al. (2009)'Interactions between gastric acid secretagogues and the localization of the gastrin receptor',Scandinavian Journal of Gastroenterology,44:4,390 — 393</ref> Gastrin itself has no effect on the maximum histamine-stimulated gastric acid secretion.<ref>Kleveland PM, Waldum HL, Larsson M. Gastric acid secretion in the totally isolated, vascularly perfused rat stomach. A selective muscarinic-1 agent does, whereas gastrin does not, augment maximal histamine-stimulated acid secretion. Scand J Gastroenterol 1987;/22:/705�13.</ref>

The effect of histamine, acetylcholine and gastrin is synergistic, that is, effect of two simultaneously is more than additive of effect of the two individually. It helps in non-linear increase of secretion with stimuli physiologically.<ref>{{Cite book|title = Ganong's Review of Medical Physiology 24th edition|last = |first = |publisher = LANGE|year = |isbn = |location = |pages = }}</ref>
-->

==內在因子==
{{see also|內在因子}}

胃壁細胞也產生[[內在因子|內在因子]]。<!--Intrinsic factor is required for the absorption of [[Vitamin_B12|vitamin B{{ssub]] in the diet.  A long-term deficiency in vitamin B<sub>12</sub> can lead to [[megaloblastic_anemia|megaloblastic anemia]], characterized by large fragile [[Red_blood_cell|erythrocyte]]s. [[Pernicious_anaemia|Pernicious anaemia]] results from autoimmune destruction of gastric parietal cells, precluding the synthesis of intrinsic factor and, by extension, absorption of Vitamin B<sub>12</sub>. Pernicious anemia also leads to megaloblastic anemia. [[Atrophic_gastritis|Atrophic gastritis]], particularly in the elderly, will cause an inability to absorb B<sub>12</sub> and can lead to deficiencies such as decreased DNA synthesis and [[nucleotide|nucleotide]] metabolism in the bone marrow.
-->

==小管==
小管是胃壁細胞中所發現的一種匹配性生物構造。<!--It is a deep infolding, or little channel, which serves to increase the surface area, e.g. for secretion.  The parietal cell membrane is dynamic; the numbers of canaliculi rise and fall according to secretory need.  This is accomplished by the fusion of canalicular precursors, or "tubulovesicles", with the membrane to increase surface area, and the reciprocal endocytosis of the canaliculi (reforming the tubulovesicles) to decrease it.-->

== 胃壁細胞的疾病 ==
